texts.text: >The Liberators return to the stairs and continue climbing.
This is bad... My legs might not hold out much longer...
The door to this floor seems to be open...
Aight, let's go in...
Yo, I'm guessin' this is our next trial...
Ah, Liberators, you have arrived.
It's you... Elohim!
So this is what Vince saw when he got sent to that parallel world.
I, Elohim, shall administer your second trial to you.
You are to defeat me if you can.
>As Elohim says that, its surroundings become engulfed in light.

Shit...!
It's just gonna wipe us out all at once?!

We can't let that happen!
Devil Download!
Die!
*Groan*
>The demon disappears as it tries to defend against Elohim's attack.
Geez...
Why do you resist erasure?
Do you not seek salvation?
This world is doomed to be destroyed by Vanitas.
And this is a chance to deal with all these humans who live and breathe malice.
Now is the time to act.
Hah! You haven't changed at all!
Yo, this guy's a real piece of work, huh? Worse than what I expected.
I can see why you hate this thing's guts.
It's like it thinks all humans are completely worthless.
Salvation through erasure? So in your mind, our lives are a living hell?
Be it you or Shaddai,
you guys love pushing people around when they haven't even asked for your help, huh?
That just means you're both a nuisance, you know?!

Aight, Liberators!
Time to Elohim who's boss!
Devil Download!!
Fools. Fight me all at once if you dare.
*Roar*
>The Liberators attack all at once!
>But Elohim quickly counters everything that's thrown at it.
No!
You've gotta be kidding me!
I thought we at least put a dent in it...
But nothing seems to have worked.
Shit, Elohim's gotten stronger compared to before...!
You will never be able to defeat me, a part of God himself, at this rate.
You shall perish knowing how foolish you are!
>The battle between the Liberators and Elohim rages on.
>Meanwhile, Shaddai and Sabaoth observe from a distance...
The Liberators appear to be struggling quite a bit.
This was to be expected.
Unlike us, Elohim is actively attempting to erase all that is.
You wish for something else?
Those who are weaker than my minions need not live.
Elohim seeks an entirely different goal. To destroy anything and everything.
A different goal...
You have been watching over these humans for some time now.
And yet, you appear to be willing to let them fall to Elohim now.
Why is that?
What is your goal, Shaddai?
Why place these humans in such an undesirable situation?
Elohim the Godly...
The incarnation of the trial that "no human will be able to pass".
Yey they proved their strength to me and overcame the trial I set before them.
Still, there are certain tests that no human has any hope of passing.
There is only one thing humans can do when they are faced with a hopeless or dire situation.
Pray.
Pray to God as a last resort.
Faith and prayer alone will allow them to pass this trial...
That is what the true children of God are supposed to do.
But...
>Shaddai peers towards the Liberators.

There is no use!
Give up!
>Elohim conjures up a massive ball of heat.
Newbie, watch out!!

Oh no you don't!
You, go help them!
On my way!
There!
Thank you!
You saved me.

That's right!
Honey's just that great!
Nice work, Honey!
Aight, Liberators, just hang in there a litte longer!

Yo, we ain't alone!
We've got each other!
We're gonna kick Elohim's ass together!
Copy that!
We cannot ignore "that one"...
Yes, she's... A Homunculus?
Indeed.
Proof of humanity creating life. Proof that they have set foot into the realm of God.
He, the great creator, will not be pleased with this.
Not only that, any alliance between her and humanity is pure blasphemy.
However...
These humans have proved that they are worthy of being called God's children.
They will soon come to realize their mistake.
And it is our duty to bestow upon them an opportunity to repent.
Liberators...
Fight. Pray.
Overcome this trial by maintaining your faith in God.
